{"lemma":"بَعْدُ","slug":"بَعْدُ","root":"ب.ع.د","root_slug":"ب-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَعْدُ","root":"بعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adv","noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2866"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be distant, afar, to become distant, go away (مِنْ (min) or عَنْ (ʕan) from)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to die, to perish"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعُدَ (baʕuda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dimension"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"absence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"death"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interval"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعَدَ (baʕada) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعِدَ (baʕida) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distance, going to a distance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"death"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"after"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"after that","examples":[{"text":"فَمَا يُكَذِّبُكَ بَعْدُ بِالدِّينِ","english":"So what will make you deny the religion after that?"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2866","headword_ar":"بَعْدُ","root":"bEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an adv. n. of time, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"After,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afterwards:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and allowable also, accord. to some of the grammarians, as an adv. n. of place, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabolu","text_ar":"قَبْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, K:) it is a vague adv. n., of which the meaning is not understood without its being prefixed to another noun [expressed or implied]; denoting after-time. (Msb.) When it occurs without any complement, (S, K,) a noun or the like which should be its complement being intended to be understood as to the meaning thereof but not as to the letter, (S, * TA,) it is indecl., (S, K,) because it resembles a particle, (TA,) and has damm for its termination to show that it is indecl., since it cannot have damm by any rule of desinential syntax because it cannot occur as an agent nor as an inchoative or enunciative. (S.) Sb, however, mentions [as exceptions to this rule] the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino baEodK","text_ar":"مِنْ بَعْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Afterwards"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu h`*aA baEodFA","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ هٰذَا بَعْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will do this afterwards"},{"kind":"text","text":"], as having been used by the Arabs. (K, * TA.) [The latter of these phrases is common in the present day. Another exception to the rule above-mentioned will be found in what follows.] Accord. to the primary rule, it is used as a prefixed n. governing its complement in the gen. case; (S;) [i. e., it is used in the manner of a preposition;] and when thus used, it is decl., (K,) because it does not in this case [always] resemble a particle. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a zayodN baEoda EamorKw","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ زَيْدٌ بَعْدَ عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd came after 'Amr."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu baEodaka","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ بَعْدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodika","text_ar":"بَعْدِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him after thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) The words of the Kur [xxx. 3],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi A@loA^amoru mino qabolu wa mino baEodu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ ا@لْاَمْرُ مِنْ قَبْلُ وَ مِنْ بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To God"},{"kind":"text","text":"belonged"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the command before"},{"kind":"text","text":"that the Greeks were overcome"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and after"},{"kind":"text","text":"that they had been overcome, [thus read when the complements of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbl","text_ar":"قبل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bEd","text_ar":"بعد"},{"kind":"text","text":"are intended to be understood as to the meaning thereof but not as to the letter,] are also read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qaboli wa mino baEodi","text_ar":"مِنْ قَبْلِ وَ مِنْ بَعْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", when each complement is intended to be understood as to the meaning and the letter, and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qabolK wa mino baEodK","text_ar":"مِنْ قَبْلٍ وَ مِنْ بَعْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning To God belongeth the command"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first and last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[when neither complement is intended to be understood either as to the letter or as to the meaning,] but the first of these readings is the best. (L.) [You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda *`lika","text_ar":"بَعْدَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodi *`lika","text_ar":"بَعْدِ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"After that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda A^ano faEalotu","text_ar":"بَعْدَ اَنْ فَعَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodi A^ano faEalotu","text_ar":"بَعْدِ اَنْ فَعَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda maA faEalotu","text_ar":"بَعْدَ مَا فَعَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino baEodi maA","text_ar":"مِنْ بَعْدِ مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotu","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"After I did,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after my doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing: &c.] Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otu baEodayokumaA","text_ar":"جِيْتُ بَعْدَيْكُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda kumaA","text_ar":"بَعْدَ كُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came after you two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mim~aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا مِمَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa baEodahu gaAyapN fiY Aljawodapi","text_ar":"لَيْسَ بَعْدَهُ غَايَةٌ فِى الجَوْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alr~adaA='ap","text_ar":"فِى الرَّدَا=ءَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is of the things after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond, which there is not any extreme degree in respect of goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of badness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, by way of abridgement,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa baEodahu","text_ar":"لَيْسَ بَعْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with nothing following this]: and hence, app., the saying of Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_ino","text_ar":"وَاـِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna layosa biAl~a*iY laA baEoda lahu","text_ar":"كَانَ لَيْسَ بِالَّذِى لَا بَعْدَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And though"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it be not in the utmost degree"},{"kind":"text","text":"in respect of goodness:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bEd","text_ar":"بعد"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus used as a decl. noun. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","A","K"]}]}}